<ONGOING_CHAR MODIFIED="2013-10-06 10:44:37 +0100" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]" STUDY_ID="STD-Ronning-2013">
<CHAR_STUDY_NAME MODIFIED="2013-08-01 11:04:30 +0100" MODIFIED_BY="Nicole Martin"/>
<CHAR_METHODS MODIFIED="2013-10-06 09:35:10 +0100" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>Development, initial and final evaluation of a computer-based educational programme.</P>
</CHAR_METHODS>
<CHAR_PARTICIPANTS MODIFIED="2013-10-06 10:44:37 +0100" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>Phase 1: Development:</P>
<P>2 physicians and 2 nurses (research team), multimedia developer, and adults with congenital heart disease.</P>
<P>Phase 2: Initial evaluation:</P>
<P>3 physicians, 3 nurses, and adults with congenital heart disease.</P>
<P>Phase 3: Final evaluation:</P>
<P>Adults with congenital heart disease.</P>
</CHAR_PARTICIPANTS>
<CHAR_INTERVENTIONS MODIFIED="2013-10-06 09:36:58 +0100" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>Computer-based educational programme comprising 10 modules; each module specific for 1 congenital heart abnormality (aortic valve stenosis, atrial septal defect, coarctation of the aorta, complete transposition of the great arteries, Ebstein anomaly, Eisenmenger syndrome, single ventricle, tetralogy of Fallot, ventricular septal defect).</P>
</CHAR_INTERVENTIONS>
<CHAR_OUTCOMES MODIFIED="2013-10-06 09:37:10 +0100" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>Evaluation phases: Content related to user-friendliness/usability, comprehensibility, and appearance.</P>
</CHAR_OUTCOMES>
<CHAR_STARTING_DATE MODIFIED="2013-08-01 11:04:24 +0100" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>2010</P>
</CHAR_STARTING_DATE>
<CHAR_CONTACT_INFORMATION MODIFIED="2013-08-01 11:04:30 +0100" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>Helen Ronning, Department of Cardiology, Linkoping University Hospital, S-581 85 Linkoping, Sweden.</P>
<P>Tel: +46 1011038779; Fax: +46 10103224</P>
<P>E-mail: helen.ronning@liu.se</P>
</CHAR_CONTACT_INFORMATION>
<CHAR_NOTES MODIFIED="2013-10-06 09:37:24 +0100" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>The authors are planning to publish their results including data on depression, and this will be included in a further update of this review.</P>
</CHAR_NOTES>
</ONGOING_CHAR>
